The paper deals with the problem of finding a drawing of a graph in the plane with minimum number of crossings, which is a fundamental problem in topological graph theory. This problem is closely related to the problem of minimum edge planarization, which involves removing a minimum-cardinality subset of edges from a graph to make it planar. Therefore, the paper is likely to be classified under computational geometry (cs.CG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), graph theory (cs.GT), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
